{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Geometry interfaces","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geometry_interfaces","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geometry_interfaces\">Geometry interfaces</a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Interfaces</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrix\"><code>DOMMatrix</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly\"><code>DOMMatrixReadOnly</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMPoint\"><code>DOMPoint</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMQuad\"><code>DOMQuad</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRect\"><code>DOMRect</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRectReadOnly\"><code>DOMRectReadOnly</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p><strong>Geometry interfaces</strong> is a CSS module that provides interfaces for working with 3D and 2D graphics — in particular, for working with points, rectangles, quadrilaterals and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebGL_API/Matrix_math_for_the_web#transformation_matrices\">transformation matrices</a> (for operations that translate/move, scale, rotate, skew/shear/slant, and flip graphics, as well as for multiplying/chaining and inverting/undoing those operations).</p>\n<p>As a web developer, you don't always use the geometry interfaces directly, but instead use other features that rely on them behind the scenes: parts of <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Transforms\">CSS Transforms</a>, the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API\">Canvas API</a>, the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebXR_Device_API\">WebXR Device API</a>, and (more directly) <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/VideoFrame/visibleRect\"><code>VideoFrame.visibleRect</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/getClientRects\"><code>Element.getClientRects()</code></a>, and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/getBoundingClientRect\"><code>Element.getBoundingClientRect()</code></a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"interfaces","title":"Interfaces","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"dommatrix\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrix\"><code>DOMMatrix</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Represents a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebGL_API/Matrix_math_for_the_web#transformation_matrices\">transformation matrix</a>, for operations that translate/move, scale, rotate, skew/shear/slant, and flip graphics, as well as for multiplying/chaining and inverting/undoing those operations.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"dommatrixreadonly\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly\"><code>DOMMatrixReadOnly</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Read-only version of <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrix\"><code>DOMMatrix</code></a>.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"dompoint\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMPoint\"><code>DOMPoint</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Represents a 2D or 3D point in a coordinate system; it includes values for the coordinates in up to three dimensions, as well as an optional perspective value.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"domquad\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMQuad\"><code>DOMQuad</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Represents a collection of four <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMPoint\"><code>DOMPoint</code></a> objects defining the corners of a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quadrilateral\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">quadrilateral</a>.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"domrect\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRect\"><code>DOMRect</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Represents the size and position of a rectangle.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"domrectreadonly\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRectReadOnly\"><code>DOMRectReadOnly</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Read-only version of <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRect\"><code>DOMRect</code></a>.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Path2D/addPath\"><code>Path2D.addPath()</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasPattern/setTransform\"><code>CanvasPattern.setTransform()</code></a> articles have examples that use some of the geometry interfaces.</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"query":"api.DOMMatrix,api.DOMMatrixReadOnly,api.DOMPoint,api.DOMQuad,api.DOMRect,api.DOMRectReadOnly","specifications":[]}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"data":null,"query":"api.DOMMatrix,api.DOMMatrixReadOnly,api.DOMPoint,api.DOMQuad,api.DOMRect,api.DOMRectReadOnly","browsers":null}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Path2D/addPath\"><code>Path2D.addPath()</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasPattern/setTransform\"><code>CanvasPattern.setTransform()</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasRenderingContext2D/getTransform\"><code>CanvasRenderingContext2D.getTransform()</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasRenderingContext2D/setTransform\"><code>CanvasRenderingContext2D.setTransform()</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CSSTransformValue/toMatrix\"><code>CSSTransformValue.toMatrix()</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CSSTransformComponent/toMatrix\"><code>CSSTransformComponent.toMatrix()</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/getBoundingClientRect\"><code>Element.getBoundingClientRect()</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/getClientRects\"><code>Element.getClientRects()</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/VideoFrame/visibleRect\"><code>VideoFrame.visibleRect</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRLightEstimate\"><code>XRLightEstimate</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRRigidTransform\"><code>XRRigidTransform</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Interfaces","id":"interfaces"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"Geometry interfaces is a CSS module that provides interfaces for working with 3D and 2D graphics — in particular, for working with points, rectangles, quadrilaterals and transformation matrices (for operations that translate/move, scale, rotate, skew/shear/slant, and flip graphics, as well as for multiplying/chaining and inverting/undoing those operations).","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:10:34.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/geometry_interfaces","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/geometry_interfaces/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/1511e914c6b1ce6f88056bfefd48a6aa585cebce","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geometry_interfaces","title":"Geometry interfaces"}],"pageTitle":"Geometry interfaces - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}